window.bookSummaryJSON = "Aunt Emily is a famous mystery writer living in the Massachusetts town of New Fairfax. Alyssa is her niece, who has lived with her aunt since her parents were killed in an airplane accident when she was in her teens. Alyssa is a reporter for a local newspaper. <i>Deadly Encounters </i>contains their first three mystery cases. In <i>The Golf Club Murders,</i> those planning to develop a local golf course for residential housing are being murdered with golf clubs. Since this property might be a native American burial site, the question arises whether this Is a protest by enraged golfers or a native American uprising. Alyssa finds herself in danger in <i>The Death of a Jealous Rival</i>. Is it because she's written a story exposing a gang of shoplifters or because a rival wants her boyfriend, who has a questionable past? In <i>Old Lovers Never Die</i>, Aunt Emily wonders whether she wants a more stable relationship with a man now that she is in her fifties. This question becomes more poignant and pressing as her selection of prospects dwindles. These stories are for you if you enjoy cozy mysteries with an edge."; 
